  "description": "Official 11e terrain layouts (40kdc conversion, docs/40KDC_TERRAIN_MIGRATION_SPEC.md): loads the converted disruption_vs_purge_the_foe_1 layout into a live shooting-phase game, asserts all 44 polygon pieces reach the runtime with exact transposed geometry, and drives two real terrain interactions. (1) LoS: the Contemptor-Achillus Dreadnought's eligible-target list (the same RulesEngine query the shooting UI uses) keeps the clear-lane Kommandos but loses Boyz E, and model_visible_11e confirms the converted obscuring area blocks that sight line. (2) 14.01 terrain-as-objective: with legacy layout_1 the Shield-Captain (OC 2, unshocked, 1.42\" from the marker) controls obj_center via the classic 3.79\" radius (control=1); after the swap a Center-linked terrain area covers the objective, so only models on the area count — the Telemon and Caladius are first parked far away (being 'within' an area is any part of the base overlapping it, and both big bases graze trapezoid-1's edges from outside), leaving the battle-shocked Dreadnought as sole occupant of the save-restored single area_at area (no source_pieces), and control flips to 0. (3) Linked-pair union: re-deriving objectives from the loaded layout gives obj_center its two source_pieces (both centre trapezoids count as ONE objective), and control flips to 1 — the Shield-Captain stands in the OTHER trapezoid (area-trapezoid-2) and now counts.",
